SIMPLE: exemplary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exemplary
<hw>Ex"em*pla*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exemplaris</ets>, fr. <ets>exemplar</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>exemplaire</ets>. See <er>Exemplar</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Serving as a pattern; deserving to be proposed for imitation;
commendable; <as>as, an <ex>exemplary</ex> person; <ex>exemplary</ex>
conduct.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Bishops'] lives and doctrines ought to be
<qex>exemplary</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Serving as a warning; monitory; <as>as,
<ex>exemplary</ex> justice, punishment, or damages</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Illustrating as the proof of a thing.</def>
<rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Exemplary damages</b></col>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Damage</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exemplary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Exemplary
<hw>Ex"em*pla*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An exemplar; also, a copy of a
book or writing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exemplifiable</ent>⟦br⟧
